[2026-07-20T06:21:58.692Z] [INFO]     "result": "# Ignore Option Handling\n\nThe `ignore` option accepts **both functions and string/RegExp patterns**.\n\n## Accepted Types\n\nThe `validateOptsIgnore` function converts the input to an array format: `\"if (ignore) { return Array.isArray(ignore) ? ignore : [ignore]; }\"` This allows a single value or array of values.\n\nDuring application, the code checks: `\"if (typeof ignore === 'function') { return ignore(filePath); } return filePath.match(ignore);\"` This demonstrates that each ignore entry can be either a callable function that receives the file path, or a pattern that's matched against the path string.\n\n## Application Location\n\nThe ignore logic is applied in the `signApplication` function through the `shouldIgnoreFilePath` helper. This function iterates through the `opts.ignore` array and tests each file path before signing operations occur. Files matching any ignore condition are skipped with a debug log: `\"Skipped... \" + filePath`.\n\nThe filtering happens **after** the file tree walk completes but **before** codesigning, not during the initial directory traversal itself.",
