[2026-07-20T06:22:30.392Z] [INFO]         "content": "# How `opts.ignore` is Used\n\n## Implementation Details\n\nThe `shouldIgnoreFilePath` function processes `opts.ignore` to filter paths during the signing process:\n\n```javascript\nfunction shouldIgnoreFilePath(filePath) {\n    if (opts.ignore) {\n        return opts.ignore.some(function (ignore) {\n            if (typeof ignore === 'function') {\n                return ignore(filePath);\n            }\n            return filePath.match(ignore);\n        });\n    }\n    return false;\n}\n```\n\n## Function Support\n\n**Yes, functions are supported.** The code checks `typeof ignore === 'function'` and executes the callback, passing the file path as an argument.\n\n## Filtering Behavior\n\nThe function filters paths from two sources:\n1. **Child paths** - obtained via `walkAsync((0, util_1.getAppContentsPath)(opts))`\n2. **Additional binaries** - from `opts.binaries` array\n\nEach path is tested sequentially. If a match is found (either through function execution or regex matching), the path is skipped during the signing operation with the message `'Skipped... ' + filePath`.\n\nThe validation function `validateOptsIgnore` normalizes single values into an array format before processing."
